intelServerBaseboard7.name: intelServerBaseboard7
intelServerBaseboard7.description: This SNMP MIB module supports the Intel Server Baseboard SNMP subagent for monitoring baseboard components, providing SNMP access to GET information for baseboard components, SET sensor thresholds and support events through the NOTIFICATION-TYPE construct. Version: 2.0 9/15/2012 Intel copyright information 2012/2013

physicalMemoryDeviceAssociatedArray.description: This attribute defines the associated array of the Physical Memory Device.

physicalMemoryDeviceTotalWidth.name: physicalMemoryDeviceTotalWidth
physicalMemoryDeviceTotalWidth.description: This attribute defines the total width in bits of the Physical Memory Device, including any check or error correction bits. If there are no error correction bits, this value should be equal to data width. If the width is unknown, the field is set to FFFFh.

physicalMemoryDeviceDataWidth.name: physicalMemoryDeviceDataWidth
physicalMemoryDeviceDataWidth.description: This attribute defines the width in bits of the Physical Memory Device. A data width of 0 and a total width of 8 indicates that the device is being used solely to provide 8 error correction bits. If the width is unknown, the field is set to FFFFh.

physicalMemoryDeviceSize.name: physicalMemoryDeviceSize
physicalMemoryDeviceSize.description: This attribute defines the size of the memory device in MB. If the value is 0, no memory device is installed in the socket. if the size is unknown, the field value is FFFFh. The granularity in which the value is specified depends on the setting of the most significant bit, bit 15. If the bit is 0, the value is specified in megabyte units; if the bit is 1, the value is specified in kilobyte units. For example, the value 8100h identifies a 256KM memory device and 0100h identifies a 256MB memory device.

physicalMemoryDeviceFormFactor.name: physicalMemoryDeviceFormFactor
physicalMemoryDeviceFormFactor.description: This attribute defines the form factor of the Physical Memory Device.

physicalMemoryDeviceLocator.name: physicalMemoryDeviceLocator
physicalMemoryDeviceLocator.description: The string that identifies the physically labeled socket or board position where the memory device is located.

physicalMemoryDeviceBankLabel.name: physicalMemoryDeviceBankLabel
physicalMemoryDeviceBankLabel.description: The string that identifies the physically labeled bank where the memory device is located.

physicalMemoryDeviceMemoryType.name: physicalMemoryDeviceMemoryType
physicalMemoryDeviceMemoryType.description: This attribute defines the type of the Physical Memory Device as per the SMBIOS 2.3.4 specification.

physicalMemoryDeviceTypeDetail.name: physicalMemoryDeviceTypeDetail
physicalMemoryDeviceTypeDetail.description: This attribute is bit encoded and specifies additional detail about the physical Memory Device. SMBIOS 2.3.4 specification defines that multiple bits can be set if more then one of the following attributes applies: bit 0 reserved, set to 0 bit 7 synchronous bit 1 other bit 8 CMOS bit 2 unknown bit 9 EDO bit 3 fast-paged bit 10 Window DRAM bit 4 static column bit 11 cache DRAM bit 5 pseudo-static bit 12 non-volatile bit 6 RAMBUS bits 13:15 reserves, set to 0

physicalMemoryDeviceSpeed.name: physicalMemoryDeviceSpeed

physicalMemoryDeviceSerialNumber.description: The string number for the serial number of this memory device.

physicalMemoryDeviceAssetTag.name: physicalMemoryDeviceAssetTag
physicalMemoryDeviceAssetTag.description: The string number for the asset tag of this memory device.

physicalMemoryDevicePartNumber.name: physicalMemoryDevicePartNumber
physicalMemoryDevicePartNumber.description: The string part number if this memory device.

coolingUnitRedundancyStatus.name: coolingUnitRedundancyStatus
coolingUnitRedundancyStatus.description: Gives the redundancy status of the Cooling Unit. 'Fully Redundan ' means that all of the configured redundancy is still available; 'Degraded Redundancy' means that some failures have been experienced but some reduced amount of redundancy is still available; 'Redundancy Lost' means that a sufficie t number of failures have been experienced that no redundancy is available and the next failure experienced within the Cooling Unit will cause overall Cooling Unit failure.

coolingDeviceUpperNonRecoverableThreshol.description: This attribute contains the fatal error threshold level for the fan. The threshold is given in the units specified by the Fan Units attribute. This attribute may not apply to all fan types. 0x7fffffff (2147483647) denotes 'unknown'.

coolingDeviceUpperCriticalThreshold.name: coolingDeviceUpperCriticalThreshold
coolingDeviceUpperCriticalThreshold.description: This attribute contains the major error threshold level for the fan. The threshold is given in the units specified by the Fan Units attribute. This attribute may not apply to all fan types. 0x7fffffff (2147483647) denotes 'unknown'.

coolingDeviceUpperNonCriticalThreshold.name: coolingDeviceUpperNonCriticalThreshold
coolingDeviceUpperNonCriticalThreshold.description: This attribute contains the warning threshold level for the fan. The threshold is given in the units specified by the Fan Units attribute. This attribute may not apply to all fan types. 0x7fffffff (2147483647) denotes 'unknown'.

coolingDeviceLowerNonCriticalThreshold.name: coolingDeviceLowerNonCriticalThreshold
coolingDeviceLowerNonCriticalThreshold.description: This attribute contains the lower warning threshold level for the fan. The threshold is given in the units specified by the Fan Units attribute. This attribute may not apply to all fan types. 0x7fffffff (2147483647) denotes 'unknown'.

coolingDeviceLowerCriticalThreshold.name: coolingDeviceLowerCriticalThreshold
coolingDeviceLowerCriticalThreshold.description: This attribute contains the lower critical threshold level for the fan. The threshold is given in the units specified by the Fan Units attribute. This attribute may not apply to all fan types. 0x7fffffff (2147483647) denotes 'unknown'.

coolingDeviceLowerNonRecoverableThreshol.name: coolingDeviceLowerNonRecoverableThreshold
coolingDeviceLowerNonRecoverableThreshol.description: This attribute contains the fatal error threshold level for the fan. The threshold is given in the units specified by the Fan Units attribute. This attribute may not apply to all fan types. 0x7fffffff (2147483647) denotes 'unknown'.

coolingDeviceResolution.name: coolingDeviceResolution

coolingDeviceTolerance.name: coolingDeviceTolerance
coolingDeviceTolerance.description: This attribute describes the sensor's tolerance in the units specified by the cooling device's units attrubite. 0x7fffffff (2147483647) denotes 'unknown'.

coolingDeviceAccuracy.name: coolingDeviceAccuracy
coolingDeviceAccuracy.description: This attribute describes the sensor's accuracy in +/- hundredth of a percent. 0x7fffffff (2147483647) denotes 'unknown'.
